track_notes: Follow tarmac track to farm entrance, turn right up hill on path.  Continue around into side valley.  Turn left to cross the footbridge (hand rail on once side only). The follow the obvious path up and right, passing through some very boggy areas lower down. Near the top the path becomes very rocky and bouldery.  You will then reach a stone circle on the summit.
For track detail notes see same track on GW/NW-003

Total time (including ops): 9hr 50m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Elidir Fawr Circuit via Glyders from Gwern Gof Isaf. Aug 2020.

track_notes:
Park in gravel layby just before gate on reservoir access road.
Proceed along road to Marchllyn Bach, go through gate to reservoir then immediately turn right and head up the hill with the fence on your right, steep initially but eases off as you approach the summit of Elidir Fawr.
Turn left, head towards corner of fence then follow fence keeping it on your right hand side.  Path becomes steep and gravelly and well defined as it zig zags up to the ridge.
Turn left and follow ridge with some climbing over boulders needed to reach stone shelter at the summit.
Head east to descend along well defined path with multiple options in places.  I kept right on the more defined path to head to Y Garn but less well used path on the left takes you direct to Mynydd Perfedd.
Follow path along grassy/rocky plain to summit of Carnedd y Filiast to the right of the boulder wall.
Path then zig zags down to the saddle point, keep left to drop down to the reservoir access road leading down to parking spot.
track_title: Circular route via Elidir Fach and Carnedd y Filiast
